==English==

===Etymology===
From {{ang}} [[wealdan]], from Germanic ''*walt-''.  Cognate with German [[walten]], Swedish [[vålla]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/wi:ld/}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# ''(obsolete)'' to [[command]]; To [[possess]] or [[own]].
# ''(obsolete except in Scots)'' To [[control]], to [[guide]] or [[manage]].
# To handle with skill and ease, especially of a weapon or tool.
# To exercise (authority or influence) effectively.

